#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:49
msgid ""
"The MCP AI Assistant uses [**Pattern 2 — `operaton-mcp` via `engine-rest`**]"
"{1} from the Operaton Access Patterns reference. The `operaton-mcp` "
"subprocess talks **directly to Operaton's `engine-rest` API**, bypassing the "
"RONL Business API entirely. It receives the full, unfiltered Operaton "
"surface — all process instances, all deployments, all tenants — with no "
"organisation filter applied."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:51
msgid ""
"In `mcpClient.service.ts`, the `StdioClientTransport` spawns the `operaton-"
"mcp` child process and passes it the following env vars directly from the "
"backend configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:52
msgid ""
"OPERATON_BASE_URL: config.operaton.baseUrl,   // → OPERATON_BASE_URL (must "
"end with /engine-rest)\n"
"OPERATON_USERNAME: config.operaton.username,\n"
"OPERATON_PASSWORD: config.operaton.password,"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:58
msgid ""
"Authentication is **basic auth** — unlike the standalone external `operaton-"
"mcp` configuration described in the access patterns page, which uses OIDC "
"client credentials. Because the AI assistant runs as an embedded backend "
"subprocess, it inherits the backend's own Operaton service account "
"credentials rather than an independent Keycloak client."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:60
msgid ""
"!!! warning \"OPERATON_BASE_URL must point at engine-rest\" Setting "
"`OPERATON_BASE_URL` to the RONL Business API base URL (e.g. `https://"
"acc.api.open-regels.nl`) will break every MCP tool call. The AI assistant "
"requires the native `engine-rest` path structure — routes like `/process-"
"instance`, `/history/process-instance`, and `/deployment` must resolve "
"directly on the Operaton host. See [Why the patterns are incompatible]{1}."
msgstr ""

